  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through various methods, including:\n\n1. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws\n- Requiring financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Implementing Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Establishing reporting thresholds for cash transactions\n\n2. Investigation Techniques\n- Financial forensic analysis\n- Tracing money trails\n- Collaboration between law enforcement agencies\n- Using advanced technological tools and data analytics\n\n3. Prosecution Strategies\n- Targeting multiple levels of criminal networks\n- Seizure of assets\n- Criminal and civil penalties\n- International cooperation and extradition agreements\n\n4. Regulatory Oversight\n- Monitoring financial institutions\n- Implementing strict compliance requirements\n- Imposing significant fines for non-compliance\n\nThese approaches aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
